# ============================================
# 🔥 FIREBASE CONFIGURATION
# ============================================
#
# 1. Create a .env file in the project root (same folder as this file)
# 2. Add the following variables with your Firebase credentials:
#
# ============================================

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your-api-key-here
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project-id.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project-id.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your-messaging-sender-id
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your-app-id

# ============================================
# HOW TO GET YOUR FIREBASE CREDENTIALS:
# ============================================
#
# 1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com
# 2. Click "Create a project" or select existing
# 3. Name your project (e.g., "freshcart-grocery")
# 4. Disable Google Analytics (optional for this app)
# 5. Click "Create project"
#
# 6. Once created, click the gear icon ⚙️ > "Project settings"
# 7. Scroll down to "Your apps" section
# 8. Click the web icon </> to add a web app
# 9. Register app with a nickname (e.g., "FreshCart Web")
# 10. DON'T check "Set up Firebase Hosting" yet
# 11. Click "Register app"
# 12. Copy the firebaseConfig object values to the .env file above
#
# 13. Go to "Firestore Database" in left sidebar
# 14. Click "Create database"
# 15. Choose "Start in test mode" (for development)
# 16. Select a location closest to your users
# 17. Click "Enable"
#
# 18. Go to "Authentication" in left sidebar
# 19. Click "Get started"
# 20. Enable "Anonymous" sign-in method (for simple setup)
# 21. Click "Save"
#
# ============================================
# YOUR APP IS NOW CONNECTED TO FIREBASE! 🎉
# ============================================

# ============================================
# DEPLOYMENT OPTIONS:
# ============================================
#
# Option 1: Firebase Hosting (Recommended)
# - Run: npm install -g firebase-tools
# - Run: firebase login
# - Run: firebase init hosting
# - Run: npm run build
# - Run: firebase deploy
#
# Option 2: Vercel
# - Push code to GitHub
# - Import project in vercel.com
# - Add environment variables
# - Deploy
#
# Option 3: Netlify
# - Push code to GitHub
# - Import project in netlify.com
# - Add environment variables
# - Deploy
#
# ============================================